message_1:
Determine the rank of the following matrix:

\begin{bmatrix}
  1 & 2 & 3 \\
  4 & 5 & 6 \\
  7 & 8 & 9 \\
\end{bmatrix}

message_2:
To find the rank of the matrix, we need to perform Gaussian elimination to find the row echelon form and count the number of non-zero rows.

Original matrix:
\begin{bmatrix}
  1 & 2 & 3 \\
  4 & 5 & 6 \\
  7 & 8 & 9 \\
\end{bmatrix}

Step 1: Subtract 4 times the first row from the second row, and subtract 7 times the first row from the third row.

\begin{bmatrix}
  1 & 2 & 3 \\
  0 & -3 & -6 \\
  0 & -6 & -12 \\
\end{bmatrix}

Step 2: Divide the second row by -3.

\begin{bmatrix}
  1 & 2 & 3 \\
  0 & 1 & 2 \\
  0 & -6 & -12 \\
\end{bmatrix}

Step 3: Add 6 times the second row to the third row.

\begin{bmatrix}
  1 & 2 & 3 \\
  0 & 1 & 2 \\
  0 & 0 & 0 \\
\end{bmatrix}

The row echelon form of the matrix has 2 non-zero rows. Therefore, the rank of the matrix is 2.
